# .gitignore recommendations for DRY component system

# If using PYTHON BUILD SCRIPT approach:
# Commit your source files with {{HEADER}} and {{FOOTER}} placeholders
# The build.py script processes them and updates the files
# Nothing extra to ignore - just commit everything as normal

# If using JAVASCRIPT INJECTION approach:
# Everything is committed as-is
# No build artifacts to ignore

# General recommendations for any static site:
node_modules/
.DS_Store
*.swp
*.swo
*~
.vscode/settings.json  # VS Code personal settings (keep extensions in repo)

# If you add optional build tools later:
dist/                  # If you minify CSS/JS
build/                 # If you add a separate build directory
.env                   # Environment files if you add them
*.pyc                  # Python cache if running build.py
__pycache__/           # Python cache directory
